Reasoning: 
1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with the complexity of model-checking problems for various formalisms including first-order logic and linear mu-calculus. 
2. cs.LOgic (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely sub-category as the paper focuses on the verification of regular properties using formal languages and automata theory. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with counter systems, which are a type of data structure. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the verification of properties on operational models, which are related to programming languages. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible sub-category as the paper characterizes the complexity of model-checking problems for various formalisms.
